{"title_page": "Reliance Group", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|Reliance Industries Limited}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{more citations needed|date=January 2016}}\n{{update|date=August 2018}}\n{{COI|date=November 2019}}\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2013}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2013}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Reliance Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group. \n| logo = Reliance_Group.png\n| logo_size = 260px\n| type = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| industry = [[Conglomerate (company)|Conglomerate]]\n| predecessor = carved out from [[Reliance Industries]]\n| founded = {{start date and age|10 July 2006}}\n| founder = [[Anil Ambani]]\n| location_city = Reliance Centre, Santacruz (East), [[Mumbai]]\n| key_people = [[Anil Ambani]] <br>{{small|(Chairman)}} <br>\n| products = Financial services, construction, entertainment, Power, health care, aviation, Defense\n| revenue = {{profit}} {{USD}}15.4 billion (2012){{citation needed|date=January 2016}}\n| operating_income = {{profit}} {{USD}}2 billion (2012){{citation needed|date=January 2016}}\n| net_income = {{profit}} {{USD}}3.5 billion (2012){{citation needed|date=January 2016}}\n| assets = {{profit}} {{USD}}43.6 billion (2016) {{cite web | url = http://reliancecapital.co.in/pdf/Rcap_Abridged_Annual_Report_2015_16.pdf | title = '}}\n| num_employees = 75,000 (March 2018)\n| subsid = [[Reliance Power]]<br>[[Reliance Infrastructure]]<br>[[Reliance Capital]]<br>[[Reliance Entertainment]]<br>[[Reliance Health]]<br>[[Reliance MediaWorks]]\n| location_country = India\n| homepage = {{URL|http://www.reliancegroupindia.com/}}\n|  \n}}\n\n'''Reliance Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group''' or '''Reliance Group''' is an Indian [[Conglomerate (company)|conglomerate]], headquartered in [[Mumbai]], India. The company, which was formed after [[Dhirubhai Ambani]]'s business was divided up, is headed by his younger son [[Anil Ambani]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iloveindia.com/economy-of-india/top-50-companies/reliance-adag.html |title=Reliance Group \u2013 Reliance Anil dmsumra 7Dhirubhai Ambani Group India \u2013 Reliance Group Profile |publisher=Iloveindia.com |date=21 July 2007 |accessdate=14 August 2010}}</ref> \n\nReliance Group has six listed companies. [[Reliance Power]], [[Reliance Infrastructure]], [[Reliance Capital]], [[Reliance Entertainment]], Reliance Home Finance and [[Reliance Health]]. The group provides financial services, construction, entertainment, power, health care, manufacturing, defence, aviation, and transportation services.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.in/anil-ambani-companies-a-complete-list-of-all-the-ventures-he-owns/articleshow/69900793.cms|title=Here's a look at all the companies that Anil Ambani owns|website=Business Insider|access-date=2019-10-28}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n{{main|Dhirubhai Ambani}}\nReliance Commercial Corporation was founded by [[Dhirubhai Ambani]] in 1966 as a [[polyester]] firm. It got renamed as [[Reliance Industries]] on May 08, 1973. Reliance later entered into financial services, petroleum refining, power sector. By 2002 Reliance had grown into a U$15 billion [[Conglomerate (company)|conglomerate]]. After the death of Dhirubhai Ambani on 6 July 2002, Reliance was headed by his two sons. The Reliance ADA Group was formed in 2006 after the two brothers [[Mukesh Ambani]] and [[Anil Ambani]], split [[Reliance Industries]] in December 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://business.rediff.com/report/2010/jun/18/reliance-mukesh-ambani-confirms-truce-with-anil.htm |title=Mukesh to double enterprise value to US$160 bn: Rediff.com Business |publisher=Business.rediff.com |date=18 June 2010 |accessdate=14 August 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiadaily.com/editorial/11-26c-04.asp |title=Reliance set to split between Anil and Mukesh Ambani \u2013 Central Government may intervene! |publisher=IndiaDaily |accessdate=14 August 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081009153627/http://www.indiadaily.com/editorial/11-26c-04.asp |archivedate=9 October 2008 }}</ref> Anil Ambani got the responsibility of [[Reliance Infocomm]], [[Reliance Energy]] and [[Reliance Capital]]. Reliance Group entered the power sector through [[Reliance Power]], and the entertainment sector by acquiring Adlabs. In October 2010, Reliance power placed world's largest order worth $8.29 billion to [[Shanghai Electric Group]] to supply power equipment based on [[Supercritical steam generator]] technology.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://in.reuters.com/article/idINIndia-52506320101028 |title=Reliance Power, Shanghai Electric ink $8.3 bln deal | publisher=Reuters |website=in.reuters.com |date=28 October 2010 |accessdate=28 July 2016}}</ref> On 28 October 2017, the group launched construction of a defense production unit in [[Multi-modal International Cargo Hub and Airport at Nagpur|Mihan-SEZ]] region.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/reliance-dassault-jv-to-start-output-in-q1-of-2018/articleshow/61280299.cms |title=Reliance-Dassault JV to start output in Q1 of 2018 |publisher=/timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=28 Oct 2018 }}</ref> The unit will be part of a joint venture between Reliance Group, led by Anil Ambani, and its JV partner French major [[Dassault Aviation]]. The production at Mihan-SEZ will begin with components for the [[Dassault Rafale|Rafale]] warplanes and [[Dassault Falcon|Falcon]] business jet produced by Dassault. It is expected to fully assemble both the aircraft in the [[Nagpur]] unit in the coming years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/dhirubhai-1932-2002/216338|title=Dhirubhai, 1932-2002|website=https://www.outlookindia.com/|access-date=2019-10-28}}</ref>\n\n; Subsidiaries\n* [[Reliance Infrastructure]]\n* [[Mumbai Metro]]\n* [[Reliance Roads]]\n* [[Reliance Power]]\n* [[Reliance Capital]]\n* [[Reliance Naval and Engineering Limited|Reliance Naval and Engineering]]\n* Reliance Defence\n* [[Reliance Entertainment]]\n* [[Kokilaben Dhirubhai Ambani Hospital]]\n*Reliance Health Insurance Limited\n\n==Major acquisitions==\n\n{{unreferenced section|date=February 2016}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Date !! Firm acquired !! Renamed firm\n|-\n| May 2000 || BSES<ref>{{cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/wealthmakers-the-ambanis/anil-dhirubhai-ambani-enterprises/reliance-energy/its-official-bsess-now-called-reliance-energy/articleshow/933888.cms |title=Reliance Group Takes over BSES \u2013 Reliance Anil dmsumra 7Dhirubhai Ambani Group India \u2013 Reliance Group Profile |publisher=economictimes.indiatimes.com|date=10 June 2003}}</ref>  ||  Reliance Infrastructure\n|-\n| Oct 2003 || FLAG Telecom, 207Mn$ ||  Reliance Globalcom\n|-\n| July 2005 || [[Metro Adlabs]] (51% stake), 74Mn$ ||  Reliance Entertainment\n|-\n| Apr 2008 || [[Lowry Digital]] USA, 7.5Mn$ ||  Reliance Big Entertainment\n|-\n| May 2008 || [[Vanco]] || Reliance Globalcom\n|-\n| Apr 2010 || [[Codemasters]] UK (50% stake) || Zapak\n|-\n| Sept 2011 || [[Bloomberg UTV]] (66% stake) || Reliance Capital\n|-\n| Mar 2015 || [[Pipavav Shipyard]] || Reliance Infrastructure\n|-\n| Oct 2015 || [[MTS India]] || Reliance Communication\n|}\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.reliancegroupindia.com/}}\n\n{{Reliance Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group}}\n\n[[Category: Reliance Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group| 01]]\n[[Category: Conglomerate companies of India]]\n[[Category: Companies based in Mumbai]]\n[[Category: Gas turbine manufacturers]]\n[[Category: Aircraft engine manufacturers of India]]\n[[Category: Aerospace companies of India]]\n[[Category: Conglomerate companies established in 1966]]\n[[Category: Indian companies established in 1966]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Reliance Industries Limited}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{more citations needed|date=January 2016}}\n{{update|date=August 2018}}\n{{COI|date=November 2019}}\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2013}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2013}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Reliance Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group. \n| logo = Reliance_Group.png\n| logo_size = 260px\n| type = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| industry = [[Conglomerate (company)|Conglomerate]]\n| predecessor = carved out from [[Reliance Industries]]\n| founded = {{start date and age|10 July 2006}}\n| founder = [[Anil Ambani]]\n| location_city = Reliance Centre, Santacruz (East), [[Mumbai]]\n| key_people = [[Anil Ambani]] <br>{{small|(Chairman)}} <br>\n| products = Financial services, construction, entertainment, Power, health care, aviation, Defense\n| revenue = {{profit}} {{USD}}15.4 billion (2012){{citation needed|date=January 2016}}\n| operating_income = {{profit}} {{USD}}2 billion (2012){{citation needed|date=January 2016}}\n| net_income = {{profit}} {{USD}}3.5 billion (2012){{citation needed|date=January 2016}}\n| assets = {{profit}} {{USD}}43.6 billion (2016) {{cite web | url = http://reliancecapital.co.in/pdf/Rcap_Abridged_Annual_Report_2015_16.pdf | title = '}}\n| num_employees = 75,000 (March 2018)\n| subsid = [[Reliance Power]]<br>[[Reliance Infrastructure]]<br>[[Reliance Capital]]<br>[[Reliance Entertainment]]<br>[[Reliance Health]]<br>[[Reliance MediaWorks]]\n| location_country = India\n| homepage = {{URL|http://www.reliancegroupindia.com/}}\n|  \n}}\n\n'''Reliance Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group''' or '''Reliance Group''' is an Indian [[Conglomerate (company)|conglomerate]], headquartered in [[Mumbai]], India. The company, which was formed after [[Dhirubhai Ambani]]'s business was divided up, is headed by his younger son [[Anil Ambani]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iloveindia.com/economy-of-india/top-50-companies/reliance-adag.html |title=Reliance Group \u2013 Reliance Anil dmsumra 7Dhirubhai Ambani Group India \u2013 Reliance Group Profile |publisher=Iloveindia.com |date=21 July 2007 |accessdate=14 August 2010}}</ref> \n\nReliance Group has six listed companies. [[Reliance Power]], [[Reliance Infrastructure]], [[Reliance Capital]], [[Reliance Entertainment]], Reliance Home Finance and [[Reliance Health]]. The group provides financial services, construction, entertainment, power, health care, manufacturing, defence, aviation, and transportation services.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.in/anil-ambani-companies-a-complete-list-of-all-the-ventures-he-owns/articleshow/69900793.cms|title=Here's a look at all the companies that Anil Ambani owns|website=Business Insider|access-date=2019-10-28}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n{{main|Dhirubhai Ambani}}\nReliance Commercial Corporation was founded by [[Dhirubhai Ambani]] in 1966 as a [[polyester]] firm. It got renamed as [[Reliance Industries]] on May 08, 1973. Reliance later entered into financial services, petroleum refining, power sector. By 2002 Reliance had grown into a U$15 billion [[Conglomerate (company)|conglomerate]]. After the death of Dhirubhai Ambani on 6 July 2002, Reliance was headed by his two sons. The Reliance ADA Group was formed in 2006 after the two brothers [[Mukesh Ambani]] and [[Anil Ambani]], split [[Reliance Industries]] in December 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://business.rediff.com/report/2010/jun/18/reliance-mukesh-ambani-confirms-truce-with-anil.htm |title=Mukesh to double enterprise value to US$160 bn: Rediff.com Business |publisher=Business.rediff.com |date=18 June 2010 |accessdate=14 August 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiadaily.com/editorial/11-26c-04.asp |title=Reliance set to split between Anil and Mukesh Ambani \u2013 Central Government may intervene! |publisher=IndiaDaily |accessdate=14 August 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081009153627/http://www.indiadaily.com/editorial/11-26c-04.asp |archivedate=9 October 2008 }}</ref> Anil Ambani got the responsibility of [[Reliance Infocomm]], [[Reliance Energy]] and [[Reliance Capital]]. Reliance Group entered the power sector through [[Reliance Power]], and the entertainment sector by acquiring Adlabs. In October 2010, Reliance power placed world's largest order worth $8.29 billion to [[Shanghai Electric Group]] to supply power equipment based on [[Supercritical steam generator]] technology.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://in.reuters.com/article/idINIndia-52506320101028 |title=Reliance Power, Shanghai Electric ink $8.3 bln deal | publisher=Reuters |website=in.reuters.com |date=28 October 2010 |accessdate=28 July 2016}}</ref> On 28 October 2017, the group launched construction of a defense production unit in [[Multi-modal International Cargo Hub and Airport at Nagpur|Mihan-SEZ]] region.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/reliance-dassault-jv-to-start-output-in-q1-of-2018/articleshow/61280299.cms |title=Reliance-Dassault JV to start output in Q1 of 2018 |publisher=/timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=28 Oct 2018 }}</ref> The unit will be part of a joint venture between Reliance Group, led by Anil Ambani, and its JV partner French major [[Dassault Aviation]]. The production at Mihan-SEZ will begin with components for the [[Dassault Rafale|Rafale]] warplanes and [[Dassault Falcon|Falcon]] business jet produced by Dassault. It is expected to fully assemble both the aircraft in the [[Nagpur]] unit in the coming years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/dhirubhai-1932-2002/216338|title=Dhirubhai, 1932-2002|website=https://www.outlookindia.com/|access-date=2019-10-28}}</ref>\n\n; Subsidiaries\n* [[Reliance Infrastructure]]\n* [[Mumbai Metro]]\n* [[Reliance Roads]]\n* [[Reliance Power]]\n* [[Reliance Capital]]\n* [[Reliance Naval and Engineering Limited|Reliance Naval and Engineering]]\n* Reliance Defence\n* [[Reliance Entertainment]]\n* [[Kokilaben Dhirubhai Ambani Hospital]]\n*Reliance Health Insurance Limited\n\n==Major acquisitions==\n\n{{unreferenced section|date=February 2016}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Date !! Firm acquired !! Renamed firm\n|-\n| May 2000 || BSES<ref>{{cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/wealthmakers-the-ambanis/anil-dhirubhai-ambani-enterprises/reliance-energy/its-official-bsess-now-called-reliance-energy/articleshow/933888.cms |title=Reliance Group Takes over BSES \u2013 Reliance Anil dmsumra 7Dhirubhai Ambani Group India \u2013 Reliance Group Profile |publisher=economictimes.indiatimes.com|date=10 June 2003}}</ref>  ||  Reliance Infrastructure\n|-\n| Oct 2003 || FLAG Telecom, 207Mn$ ||  Reliance Globalcom\n|-\n| July 2005 || [[Metro Adlabs]] (51% stake), 74Mn$ ||  Reliance Entertainment\n|-\n| Apr 2008 || [[Lowry Digital]] USA, 7.5Mn$ ||  Reliance Big Entertainment\n|-\n| May 2008 || [[Vanco]] || Reliance Globalcom\n|-\n| Apr 2010 || [[Codemasters]] UK (50% stake) || Zapak\n|-\n| Sept 2011 || [[Bloomberg UTV]] (66% stake) || Reliance Capital\n|-\n| Mar 2015 || [[Pipavav Shipyard]] || Reliance Infrastructure\n|-\n| Oct 2015 || [[MTS India]] || Reliance Communication\n|}\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.reliancegroupindia.com/}}\n\n{{Reliance Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group}}\n\n[[Category:Reliance Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group| 01]]\n[[Category:Conglomerate companies of India]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Gas turbine manufacturers]]\n[[Category:Aircraft engine manufacturers of India]]\n[[Category:Aerospace companies of India]]\n[[Category:Conglomerate companies established in 1966]]\n[[Category:Indian companies established in 1966]]\n", "name_user": "Chirag Varna", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reliance_Group"}
