orgios|Saridakis}} || Athletics\n| [[Athletics at the 1906 Intercalated Games|3000 metre walk]]\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}}\n| {{Sortname|Ioannis |Raisis}} || Fencing\n| [[Fencing at the 1906 Intercalated Games|\u00c9p\u00e9e masters]]\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}}\n| \"''Omilos Filomouson [[Thessaloniki]]''\"* :<br/>Georgios Vaporis<br/>Nikolaos Pindos<br/>Antonios Tegos<br/>Nikolaos Pentzikis<br/>Ioannis Kyrou<br/> Georgios Sotiriadis<br/>[[Vasilios Zarkadis]]<br/> Dimitrios Michitsopoulos<br/>Antonios Karagionidis<br/>Ioannis Abbot<br/>Ioannis Saridakis|| Football\n| [[Football at the 1906 Intercalated Games|Football]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sansimera.gr/articles/436|title=\u039c\u03b5\u03c3\u03bf\u03bb\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03b9\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1|publisher=|accessdate=24 March 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}}\n| {{Sortname|Konstantinos|Kozanitas}} || Gymnastics\n| [[Gymnastics at the 1906 Intercalated Games|Rope climbing]]\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}}\n| \"''Team [[Greek ironclad Hydra|ironclad Hydra]]''\":<br/>Dionysios Christeas<br/>Dimitrios Grous<br/>Georgios Maroulis<br/>Nikolaos Fotinakis<br/>P. Lomvardos<br/>Dimitrios Souranis<br/>Petros Mexis  || Rowing\n| [[Rowing at the 1906 Intercalated Games|Naval boats (6 men)]]\n|-\n| rowspan=2|{{bronze medal}}\n| rowspan=2|{{Sortname|Aristides|Rangavis}} ||rowspan=2| Shooting\n| [[Shooting at the 1906 Intercalated Games|25 m rapid fire pistol]]\n|-\n| [[Shooting at the 1906 Intercalated Games|50 m pistol]]\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}}\n| {{Sortname|Georgios|Skotadis}} || Shooting\n| [[Shooting at the 1906 Intercalated Games|25 m army pistol\n(standard model)]]\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}}\n| {{Sortname|Euphrosine|Paspati}} || Tennis\n| [[Tennis at the 1906 Intercalated Games|Women's singles]]\n|-\n| {{bronze medal}}\n| {{Sortname|Xenophon|Kasdaglis}}<br/>{{Sortname|Aspasia|Matsa}} || Tennis\n| [[Tennis at the 1906 Intercalated Games|Mixed doubles]]\n|-\n|}\n\n*The bronze medal won by the team of Omilos Filomouson [[Thessaloniki]] (predecessor of [[Iraklis Thessaloniki F.C.]]) is registered to Greece. The team was composed by ethnic [[Greeks]], despite the fact that the city was part of the [[Ottoman Empire]] at the time.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* http://www.tovima.gr/opinions/article/?aid=172644\n* http://www.sansimera.gr/articles/436\n*http://www.hoa.gr/article/%CE%BC%CE%AD%CF%83%CE%BF-%CE%BF%CE%BB%CF%85%CE%BC%CF%80%CE%B9%CE%AC%CE%B4%CE%B1-1906/\n\n{{Nations at the 1906 Intercalated Games}}\n\n[[Category:Nations at the 1906 Intercalated Games]]\n[[Category:Greece at the Summer Olympics by year|1906]]\n[[Category:1906 in Greek sport|Intercalated Games]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Greece at the Olympics}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{infobox country at games\n| NOC = GRE\n| NOCname = [[Hellenic Olympic Committee]]\n| games = Intercalated Olympics\n| year = 1906\n| flagcaption = \n| oldcode = \n| website = {{url|www.hoc.gr }}&nbsp;{{in lang|el|en}}\n| location = [[Athens]]\n| competitors = 312\n| sports = 13\n| flagbearer = \n| rank = 2\n| gold = 8\n| silver = 13\n| bronze = 13\n| officials = \n| appearances = \n| app_begin_year = \n| app_end_year = \n| summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Greece|competition=Summer Olympics}}\n| winterappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Greece|competition=Winter Olympics}}\n| seealso = \n}}\n\n'''[[Greece]]''' were the host nation at the '''[[1906 Intercalated Games]]''' in [[Athens]], Greece. 312 athletes, 307 men and 5 women, competed in 70 events in 13 sports.<ref name=\"sports-reference\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/GRE/summer/1906/ |title=Greece at the 1906 Intercalated Games |access-date=21 December 2014 |work=sports-reference.com |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221214426/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/GRE/summer/1906/ |archive-date=21 December 2014  }}</ref>\n\n==Medalists==\n{| class=\"wikitabl