{"title_page": "2002\u201303 Divizia B", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n | country            = {{ROU}}\n | competition        = [[Divizia B]]\n | season             = 2002\u201303\n | teams              = 32 (2x16)\n | promoted           = \n | relegated          = \n | league topscorer   = \n | biggest home win   = \n | biggest away win   = \n | highest scoring    = \n | matches            = \n | total goals        = \n | longest wins       = \n | longest unbeaten   = \n | longest losses     = \n | highest attendance = \n | lowest attendance  = \n | average attendance = \n | prevseason = [[2001\u201302 Divizia B|2001\u201302]]\n | nextseason = [[2003\u201304 Divizia B|2003\u201304]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2002\u201303 Divizia B''' was the 63rd season of [[Divizia B]], the second tier of the [[Romanian football league system]]. It was the last in this format (two series of 16 teams each).\n\nThe winner of each series of the [[Divizia B]] was promoted to the [[Divizia A]] and the runner up from each series played a playoff (home-away) against the team finished 13th or 14th in the [[2002\u201303 Divizia A|Divizia A]]. The bottom three teams were relegated to the [[Divizia C]].\n\n== Standings ==\n=== Seria I ===\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=PR\n\n|team1=PET|name_PET=[[FC Petrolul Ploie\u0219ti|Petrolul Ploie\u0219ti]]\n|team2=GLO|name_GLO=[[FC Gloria Buz\u0103u|Gloria Buz\u0103u]]\n|team3=ONE|name_ONE=[[FC One\u0219ti]]\n|team4=MID|name_MID=[[CS N\u0103vodari|Midia N\u0103vodari]]\n|team5=PIA|name_PIA=[[FC Politehnica Ia\u0219i (1945)|Politehnica Ia\u0219i]]\n|team6=BUC|name_BUC=[[FC Rapid II Bucure\u015fti|Electromagnetica Bucure\u015fti]]\n|team7=IGB|name_IGB=[[CS Inter Gaz Bucure\u015fti|Inter Gaz Bucure\u015fti]]\n|team8=DUB|name_DUB=[[ACS Dacia Unirea Br\u0103ila|Dacia Unirea Br\u0103ila]]\n|team9=MPL|name_MPL=[[Metalul Plopeni]]\n|team10=FOC|name_FOC=[[CSM Foc\u015fani|Unirea Foc\u015fani]]\n|team11=INT|name_INT=[[FC Interna\u0