=0|gf_UMT=0|ga_UMT=0|status_UMT=R\n\n|note_GTC=[[Gilortul T\u00e2rgu C\u0103rbune\u015fti]] was excluded from the championship before the beginning of the second half of the season. All its results from the first half of the season count, however for the second half the team will lose all its games by a score of 0-3.\n|note_UMT=[[CSP UM Timi\u0219oara|UM Timi\u015foara]] was excluded from the league after the 12th round due to financial problems. The team failed to play two consecutive games. All its results have been cancelled.\n\n|col_P=green1|text_P=Promotion to [[2003\u201304 Divizia A|Divizia A]]\n|result1=P\n|col_QPP=green2|text_QPP=Qualification to [[2002\u201303 Divizia A#Relegation playoffs|promotion play-off]]\n|result2=QPP\n|col_R=red1|text_R=Relegation to [[2003\u201304 Divizia C|Divizia C]]\n|result14=R|result15=R|result16=R\n|class_rules=1) points; 2) head-to-head points; 3) head-to-head goal difference; 4) head-to-head goals scored; 5) goal difference; 6) number of goals scored.\n|update=complete\n|source=''The Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation''\n}}\n\n==Promotion / Relegation Play-off==\nThe teams placed on the 13th and 14th place in the [[Divizia A]] faced the 2nd placed teams from both groups of the [[Liga II|Divizia B]]. [[FC Politehnica AEK Timi\u0219oara|Politehnica AEK Timi\u0219oara]] and [[FC Bihor Oradea]] won the relegation play-offs.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesr/roem03.html 2002\u201303 Divizia A at RSSSF]</ref>\n\nEven though [[O\u021belul Gala\u021bi]] lost the relegation play-off against [[FC Bihor Oradea|FC Bihor]], they kept their place in the [[Divizia A]] because [[FC Petrolul Ploie\u0219ti|Petrolul Ploie\u0219ti]], the club that won the [[2002\u201303 Divizia B#Seria I|Divizia B, Seria I]], sold its promotion place to [[O\u021belul Gala\u021bi]] and merged with [[FC Astra Ploie\u0219ti|Astra Ploie\u0219ti]], the other team from the city of [[Ploie\u0219ti]], which finished on the 9th position this season.<ref>{{cite web 